<br>
What are the level requirements?<br>
40+ for melee 45+ for casters<br>
<br>
Why do casters have to be a higher level than melee classes?<br>
Spell resists, the dragon is lvl 55<br>
<br>
When a mob drops, who loots?<br>
Leader of the group that got the exp, no one else<br>
<br>
How does loot get decided?<br>
Who can use, only one lotto win per raid, random 1 200, ties reroll<br>
<br>
Who pulls the mobs?<br>
Designated pull does, usually a monk<br>
<br>
Whats the deal with buffing? When do you buff?<br>
For the dragon prep itself, all buffs off, you will go thru a line and be buffed with what is needed.  At end you camp to the chat room alreaady set up, usually karana_&lt;dragon name&gt;.<br>
<br>
Why should people listen to the raid organizers?<br>
To stay on the same page, to reduce the wait time to move to next phase.<br>
<br>
Other questions<br>
<br>
How does healing work?<br>
There is a designated area for healing, tanks at 50% should stop attack, move to that area and /shout need heal as they move. Healers should be looking for and expecting those to show up<br>
<br>
Where should first rush seek to pin the dragon?<br>
On the bridge or closer to his side, don't stop just because you got hit run to the bridge.  This will allow everyone else space and access to the dragon for the fight.  We choose the ground.<br>
<br>
Taunting<br>
If you are being hit directly by the dragon....STOP taunting. If you are not being hit by the dragon; taunt.<br>
<br>
<br>
These are my impressions on what to do, and others may differ, they are welcome to respond.  The goal here is a better dragon raid for all.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
